// RC Low-Pass Filter Analysis
// Circuit: Vin → R → Vout, C from Vout to GND
//
// Using voltage divider:
// H(s) = ZC/(R + ZC) = (1/sC)/(R + 1/sC)
//       = 1/(1 + sRC)
//
// Pole at: s = -1/RC → ωp = 1/RC
//
// Example: R=10kΩ, C=100pF
// ωp = 1/(10kΩ × 100pF) = 1/(1μs) = 1 Mrad/s
// fp = ωp/(2π) = 159 kHz
//
// At f = 159kHz: gain = -3dB, phase = -45°
// At f = 1.59MHz (10× pole): gain = -20dB, phase = -84°
// At f = 15.9kHz (0.1× pole): gain = -0.04dB, phase = -5.7°

// RC High-Pass Filter: Vin → C → Vout, R to GND
//
// Step 1: Voltage divider
// H(s) = R / (1/sC + R)
//       = sRC / (1 + sRC)
//
// Step 2: Identify poles and zeros
// Zero: numerator=0 → s=0 (at DC)
// Pole: denominator=0 → s=-1/RC → ωp=1/RC
//
// Step 3: Bode plot behavior
// ω << ωp: H ≈ jωRC → +20dB/dec, +90° phase
// ω = ωp: |H| = 1/√2 = -3dB, phase = +45°
// ω >> ωp: H ≈ 1 → 0dB, phase ≈ 0°
//
// Example: R=10kΩ, C=100pF → fp=159kHz
// At 1kHz (<<fp): gain = 20log(1k/159k) = -44dB
// At 159kHz (=fp): gain = -3dB
// At 1MHz (>>fp): gain ≈ 0dB

