// Common-Source Amplifier Small-Signal Analysis
// Circuit: VDD → RD → Vout (drain), Vin at gate, source to GND

// Replace MOSFET with small-signal model:
// - Gate: Vgs = Vin (gate tied to input)
// - Drain: current source gm×Vgs flows from drain to source
//          ro connects drain to source
//          RD connects drain to AC ground (VDD is AC ground)

// KCL at drain node (Vout):
// Current through RD: (0 - Vout)/RD = Vout downward
// Current through ro: (0 - Vout)/ro
// Current from source: gm×Vgs = gm×Vin
